title: Office of Space Commerce starts commercial pathfinder project for civil space traffic coordination system
summary: The Office of Space Commerce has selected three companies to participate in a pathfinder program that could lead to the incorporation of commercial data into its space traffic coordination system.

title: NASA SLS Exploration Upper Stage moving into qualification phase of development
summary: As NASA pushes out the schedule for Artemis II and III, development of the first major upgrade to the agency’s Space Launch System (SLS) rocket is moving into qualification. SLS Stages prime contractor Boeing is activating production areas for the new Exploration Upper Stage (EUS) at the Michoud Assembly Facility (MAF) in New Orleans in parallel with refining assembly and outfitting techniques for the stage.

title: Japan makes history with tense, successful moon landing
summary: Japan's SLIM “Moon Sniper” spacecraft made a successful lunar landing Friday, making the country just the fifth to robotically land on the moon.

title: NASA report offers pessimistic take on space-based solar power
summary: Advocates of space-based solar power are criticizing a NASA report that offered a skeptical assessment of that technology’s ability to provide low-cost green energy.

title: NASA study: clean, space-based solar power beaming is possible
summary: With commitment and investment, space-based solar power could become feasible and help reduce the world's carbon emissions.
